  <h1>Projects</h1>
  <p class="note">All of this is early and in motion; descriptions are deliberately modest.</p>

  <h2>Russia&ndash;China economic relations</h2>
  <p>
    Research internship at the Regional Institute of Security Studies (RISS),
    analysing trade flows, import dependence, and export asymmetries in the
    Russia&ndash;China relationship through customs data, with policy analysis on
    sanctions produced through RISS&rsquo;s partnership with the Royal United Services
    Institute (RUSI).
  </p>

  <h2>Varsko Intelligence</h2>
  <p>
    An early-stage project on geopolitical risk intelligence for companies exposed to
    cross-border shocks. Currently in customer discovery.
  </p>

  <h2>Global Affairs Program, Harvard IOP</h2>
  <p>
    Deputy Chair of the Institute of Politics program dedicated to global affairs,
    leading a fifty-person team that organizes events with former prime ministers,
    ambassadors, and senior policymakers, and building an internship pipeline
    connecting Harvard undergraduates with international organizations.
  </p>

  <h2>Game theory &times; geopolitics</h2>
  <p>
    A summer research apprenticeship working toward a research question on game
    theory applied to international politics &mdash; asymmetric payoffs, asymmetric
    information, and decisions that mix cooperation and defection. The writing on
    this site comes out of that work.
  </p>
</Base>
